<h1>Dropdowns</h1>
<p>
	Dropdowns allow users to select from a list and should be clearly labeled to communicate the content inside it.
	Content inside dropdowns should be grouped by relativity and ranked on importance and/or value to a user.
</p>

<section>
	<h2 id="dropdowns-composition">Dropdown composition</h2>
	<p>Dropdown component consists of 3 elements:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>dropdown container (wraps dropdown toggle and dropdown content)</li>
		<li>dropdown toggle</li>
		<li>dropdown content</li>
	</ul>
	{{#component-demo codeOnly=true}}
		<div class="wds-dropdown">
			<div class="wds-dropdown__toggle">…</div>
			<div class="wds-dropdown__content">…</div>
		</div>
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="dropdowns-interactions">Interactions</h2>
	<p>
		On desktop, dropdown content is showing whenever user hovers over dropdown toggle. For touch
		devices when user taps on a dropdown toggle you need to add
		<code class="format-code">.wds-is-active</code> class to the parent <code class="format-code">.wds-dropdown element</code>.
		There should be only one dropdown open at any time, so you should also remove this class from all the other dropdowns.
	</p>
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="dropdowns-default-variant">Default</h2>
	<p>Default dropdown, centered.</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-dropdown as |dropdown|}}
			{{#dropdown.toggle}}
				<span>Default dropdown</span>
			{{/dropdown.toggle}}
			{{#dropdown.content}}
				<ul class="wds-list">
					<li>List item 1</li>
					<li>List item 2</li>
					<li>List item 3</li>
					<li>List item 4</li>
					<li>List item 5</li>
					<li>List item 6</li>
					<li>List item 7</li>
					<li>List item 8</li>
					<li>List item 9</li>
					<li>List item 10</li>
				</ul>
			{{/dropdown.content}}
		{{/wds-dropdown}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="dropdowns-not-scrollable-variant">Not scrollable variant</h2>
	<p>
		There are special cases where we don't want a long dropdown to be scrollable, e.g. Wiki Local Navigation.
		To disable the scroll, add <code class="format-code">.wds-is-not-scrollable</code>
		to <code class="format-code">.wds-dropdown__content</code> element.
	</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-dropdown as |dropdown|}}
			{{#dropdown.toggle}}
				<span>Not scrollable dropdown</span>
			{{/dropdown.toggle}}
			{{#dropdown.content isNotScrollable=true}}
				<ul class="wds-list">
					<li>List item 1</li>
					<li>List item 2</li>
					<li>List item 3</li>
					<li>List item 4</li>
					<li>List item 5</li>
					<li>List item 6</li>
					<li>List item 7</li>
					<li>List item 8</li>
					<li>List item 9</li>
					<li>List item 10</li>
				</ul>
			{{/dropdown.content}}
		{{/wds-dropdown}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="dropdowns-right-aligned-variant">Left aligned variant</h2>
	<p>
		Dropdown aligned to the left side of the container. To align dropdown to left, you have to
		add <code class="format-code">.wds-is-left-aligned</code> class to
		<code class="format-code">.wds-dropdown__content</code> element.
	</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-dropdown as |dropdown|}}
			{{#dropdown.toggle}}
				<span>Left aligned dropdown</span>
			{{/dropdown.toggle}}
			{{#dropdown.content dropdownLeftAligned=true}}
				<ul class="wds-list">
					<li>List item 1</li>
					<li>List item 2</li>
					<li>List item 3</li>
				</ul>
			{{/dropdown.content}}
		{{/wds-dropdown}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="dropdowns-right-aligned-variant">Right aligned variant</h2>
	<p>
		Dropdown aligned to the right side of the container. To align dropdown to right, you have to add
		<code class="format-code">.wds-is-right-aligned</code> class to
		<code class="format-code">.wds-dropdown__content</code> element.
	</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-dropdown as |dropdown|}}
			{{#dropdown.toggle}}
				<span>Right aligned dropdown</span>
			{{/dropdown.toggle}}
			{{#dropdown.content dropdownRightAligned=true}}
				<ul class="wds-list">
					<li>List item 1</li>
					<li>List item 2</li>
					<li>List item 3</li>
				</ul>
			{{/dropdown.content}}
		{{/wds-dropdown}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="dropdowns-linked-list-variant">Linked list variant</h2>
	<p>
		Dropdowns that have <code class="format-code">.wds-list.wds-is-linked</code> in the content.
		Links have color and hover state different than when outside of a dropdown.
	</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-dropdown as |dropdown|}}
			{{#dropdown.toggle}}
				<span>Dropdown with linked list</span>
			{{/dropdown.toggle}}
			{{#dropdown.content isNotScrollable=true}}
				<ul class="wds-list wds-is-linked">
					<li><a href="http://fandom.wikia.com">List item 1</a></li>
					<li><a href="http://fandom.wikia.com">List item 2</a></li>
					<li><a href="http://fandom.wikia.com">List item 3</a></li>
				</ul>
			{{/dropdown.content}}
		{{/wds-dropdown}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="dropdowns-dark-variant">Dropdown with shadow</h2>
	<p>
		Dropdowns can drop shadow. To add light shadow to dropdown, you have to
		add <code class="format-code">.wds-has-shadow</code> class to
		<code class="format-code">.wds-dropdown</code> element and
		<code class="format-code">.wds-has-dark-shadow</code> to add darker shadow.
	</p>
	{{#component-demo}}
		{{#wds-dropdown hasShadow=true as |dropdown|}}
			{{#dropdown.toggle}}
				<span>Dropdown with shadow</span>
			{{/dropdown.toggle}}
			{{#dropdown.content}}
				<ul class="wds-list">
					<li>List item 1</li>
					<li>List item 2</li>
					<li>List item 3</li>
				</ul>
			{{/dropdown.content}}
		{{/wds-dropdown}}
		{{#wds-dropdown hasDarkShadow=true as |dropdown|}}
			{{#dropdown.toggle}}
				<span>Dropdown with shadow</span>
			{{/dropdown.toggle}}
			{{#dropdown.content}}
				<ul class="wds-list">
					<li>List item 1</li>
					<li>List item 2</li>
					<li>List item 3</li>
				</ul>
			{{/dropdown.content}}
		{{/wds-dropdown}}
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

